Few findings related to firstname field validations

1. Tried giving numbers in firstname field.
Request Body:
{
    "roomid": 45,
    "firstname": 1234,
    "lastname": "DEF",
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    },
    "email": "abc.def@example.com",
    "phone": "12345678900"
}
Expected Behavior:
400 status code with error message

Actual Behavior:
201 Created

Response Body:
{
    "bookingid": 5,
    "roomid": 45,
    "firstname": "1234",
    "lastname": "DEF",
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    }
}

2. Tried giving decimal in firstname field.
Request Body;
{
  "roomid": 16,
  "firstname": 12.34,
  "lastname": "DEF",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}
Expected Behavior:
400 status code with error message

Actual Behavior:
201 created

Response Body:
{
    "bookingid": 4,
    "roomid": 16,
    "firstname": "12.34",
    "lastname": "DEF",
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    }
}

3. Tried giving boolean in firstname field.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 17,
  "firstname": true,
  "lastname": "DEF",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}
Expected Behavior:
400 status code with error message

Actual Behavior:
201 created

Response Body:
{
    "bookingid": 5,
    "roomid": 17,
    "firstname": "true",
    "lastname": "DEF",
    "depositpaid": true,
    "bookingdates": {
        "checkin": "2025-11-01",
        "checkout": "2025-11-02"
    }
}

4. Tried giving special characters in firstname field. Server accepts it and booking successful.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 18,
  "firstname": “ABC@#”,
  "lastname": "DEF",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}

5. Tried giving leading and trailing spaces in firstname field. Server accepts it and booking successful.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 18,
  "firstname": " John ",
  "lastname": "DEF",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}

6. Tried giving numbers mixed in firstname field. Server accepts it and booking successful.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 19,
  "firstname": "John123",
  "lastname": "DEF",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}

7. Tried giving symbols only in firstname field. Server accepts it and booking successful.
Request Body:
{
  "roomid": 20,
  "firstname": "@#$%",
  "lastname": "DEF",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-01",
    "checkout": "2025-11-02"
  },
  "email": "abc.def@example.com",
  "phone": "12345678900"
}
